    <item>
      <title>Overview</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/overview/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/overview/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This section describes various real-life situations and issues that you may&#xA;experience with Unit.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;how-to-guides&#34;&gt;How-to guides  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#how-to-guides&#34; title=&#34;How-to guides&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/docker/&#34;&gt;Unit in Docker&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Configure a standalone Unit or a Unit-run app in a Docker&#xA;container.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/source/&#34;&gt;Building from source&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Build Unit and its language modules from source code.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/ansible/&#34;&gt;Unit in Ansible&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Use a third-party Ansible collection to automate Unit&#xA;deployment.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/integration/&#34;&gt;NGINX integration&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Front or secure Unit with NGINX.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/certbot/&#34;&gt;TLS with Certbot&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Use EFF&amp;rsquo;s Certbot with Unit to simplify certificate&#xA;manipulation.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/modules/&#34;&gt;Working with language modules&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Build new modules or prepare custom packages for&#xA;Unit.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/samples/&#34;&gt;App samples&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Reuse sample app configurations for all languages&#xA;supported by Unit.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/security/&#34;&gt;Security checklist&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Recommendations and considerations for hardening Unit.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/walkthrough/&#34;&gt;Walkthrough&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;: Follow an end-to-end guide to application configuration&#xA;in Unit.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;howto-frameworks&#34;&gt;Frameworks  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#howto-frameworks&#34; title=&#34;Frameworks&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;With Unit, you can configure a diverse range of applications based on the&#xA;following frameworks:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Unit in Docker</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/docker/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/docker/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To run your apps in a containerized Unit using the&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/installation/#installation-docker&#34;&gt;images we provide&lt;/a&gt;,&#xA;you need at least to:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Mount your application files to a directory in your container.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Publish Unit&amp;rsquo;s listener port to the host machine.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1fffb11bf8&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1fffb11bf8&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;   $ export UNIT=$(                                             \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;         docker run -d --mount type=bind,src=&amp;#34;$(pwd)&amp;#34;,dst=/www  \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;         -p 8080:8000 unit:1.34.1-python3.11                 \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;     )&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;   $ export UNIT=$(                                             \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;         docker run -d --mount type=bind,src=&amp;#34;$(pwd)&amp;#34;,dst=/www  \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;         -p 8080:8000 unit:1.34.1-python3.11                 \&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;     )&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The command mounts the host&amp;rsquo;s current directory where your app files are stored&#xA;to the container&amp;rsquo;s &lt;strong&gt;/www/&lt;/strong&gt; directory and publishes the container&amp;rsquo;s port&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;8000&lt;/strong&gt; that the listener will use as port &lt;strong&gt;8080&lt;/strong&gt; on the host,&#xA;saving the container&amp;rsquo;s ID in the &lt;code&gt;UNIT&lt;/code&gt; environment variable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Building from source</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/source/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/source/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;After you&amp;rsquo;ve obtained Unit&amp;rsquo;s&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/installation/#source&#34;&gt;source code&lt;/a&gt;, configure&#xA;and compile it to fine-tune and run a custom Unit build.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; The commands in this document starting with a hash (#) must be run as root or&#xA;with superuser privileges.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;source-prereq-build&#34;&gt;Installing Required Software  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#source-prereq-build&#34; title=&#34;Installing Required Software&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Before configuring and compiling Unit, install the required build tools and the&#xA;library files for the required languages (Go, Java, Node.js, PHP,&#xA;Perl, Python, and Ruby are supported) and all other features you want in your&#xA;Unit, such as TLS or regular expressions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Unit in Ansible</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/ansible/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/ansible/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;a href=&#34;https://galaxy.ansible.com/steampunk/unit&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Ansible collection&lt;/a&gt; by &lt;a href=&#34;https://steampunk.si&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;XLAB&#xA;Steampunk&lt;/a&gt; provides a number of Unit-related tasks&#xA;that you can use with Ansible; some of them simplify installation and setup,&#xA;while others provide common configuration steps.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ansible 2.9+ required; the collection relies on official packages and&#xA;supports Debian only.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A brief intro by the collection&amp;rsquo;s authors can be found &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.steampunk.si/unit/quickstart.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;; a behind-the-scenes&#xA;blog post is &lt;a href=&#34;https://steampunk.si/blog/why-and-how-of-the-nginx-unit-ansible-collection/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, install the collection:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1ffaca0b18&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1ffaca0b18&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; ansible-galaxy collection install steampunk.unit&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; ansible-galaxy collection install steampunk.unit&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After installation, you can use it in a playbook. Consider this&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/configuration/#python.md&#34;&gt;WSGI app&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>NGINX integration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/integration/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/integration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Unit is a potent and versatile server in its own right. However, if you&amp;rsquo;re&#xA;used to NGINX&amp;rsquo;s rich feature set, you can deploy it in front of Unit; one&#xA;notable use case for NGINX here is securing the Unit control socket.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;fronting-unit-with-nginx&#34;&gt;Fronting Unit with NGINX  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#fronting-unit-with-nginx&#34; title=&#34;Fronting Unit with NGINX&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Configure a &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/configuration/#configuration-listeners&#34;&gt;listener&lt;/a&gt; in Unit:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f2004e9ac20&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f2004e9ac20&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;127.0.0.1:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_127.0.0.1:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Socket address where NGINX proxies requests&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;pass&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_pass&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Unit&amp;#39;s internal request destination&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;forwarded&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;client_ip&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;X-Forwarded-For&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_client_ip&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;The header field set by NGINX&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;source&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;               &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;127.0.0.1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;],&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_source&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;The IP address where NGINX runs&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;127.0.0.1:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_127.0.0.1:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Socket address where NGINX proxies requests&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;pass&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;...&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_pass&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Unit&amp;#39;s internal request destination&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;forwarded&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;client_ip&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;X-Forwarded-For&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_client_ip&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;The header field set by NGINX&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;source&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;               &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;127.0.0.1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;],&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;            &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;comment_source&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;The IP address where NGINX runs&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;      &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here, &lt;strong&gt;forwarded&lt;/strong&gt; is optional; it enables identifying the&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/configuration/#configuration-listeners-xff&#34;&gt;originating IPs&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;of requests proxied from &lt;strong&gt;source&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TLS with Certbot</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/certbot/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/certbot/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To set up&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/certificates/#configuration-ssl&#34;&gt;SSL/TLS access in Unit&lt;/a&gt;,&#xA;you need certificate bundles. Although you can use self-signed certificates, it&amp;rsquo;s&#xA;advisable to obtain certificates for your website from a certificate authority&#xA;(CA). For this purpose, you may employ EFF&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href=&#34;https://certbot.eff.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Certbot&lt;/a&gt; that issues free certificates signed by &lt;a href=&#34;https://letsencrypt.org&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s&#xA;Encrypt&lt;/a&gt;, a non-profit CA.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; The commands in this document starting with a hash (#) must be run as root or&#xA;with superuser privileges.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;generating-certificates&#34;&gt;Generating certificates  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#generating-certificates&#34; title=&#34;Generating certificates&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Install &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/installation/#installation-precomp-pkgs&#34;&gt;Unit&lt;/a&gt; on your website&amp;rsquo;s server.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Working with language modules</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/modules/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/modules/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Languages supported by Unit fall into these two categories:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/modules/#modules-ext&#34;&gt;External&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;(Go, Node.js): Run outside Unit with an&#xA;interface layer to the native runtime.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/modules/#modules-emb&#34;&gt;Embedded&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;(Java, Perl, PHP, Python, Ruby, WebAssembly):&#xA;Execute in runtimes that Unit loads at startup.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For any specific language and its version, Unit needs a language module.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; The commands in this document starting with a hash (#) must be run as root or&#xA;with superuser privileges.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;modules-ext&#34;&gt;External language modules  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#modules-ext&#34; title=&#34;External language modules&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;External modules are regular language libraries or packages that you install&#xA;like any other. They provide common web functionality, communicating with Unit&#xA;from the app&amp;rsquo;s runspace.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>App samples</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/samples/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/samples/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; &lt;p&gt;These steps assume Unit was already&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/installation/#installation-precomp-pkgs&#34;&gt;installed&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;with the language module for each app.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The commands in this document starting with a hash (#) must be run as root or&#xA;with superuser privileges.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;sample-go&#34;&gt;Go  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#sample-go&#34; title=&#34;Go&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s configure the following basic app, saved as &lt;strong&gt;/www/app.go&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;go&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f2005851160&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f2005851160&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;io&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;net/http&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;unit.nginx.org/go&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;HandleFunc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;/&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;w&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;ResponseWriter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;r&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;Request&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;WriteString&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;w&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, Go on Unit!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;})&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;ListenAndServe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;kc&#34;&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-go&#34; data-lang=&#34;go&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;io&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;net/http&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;unit.nginx.org/go&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;HandleFunc&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;/&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kd&#34;&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;w&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;ResponseWriter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;r&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;http&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;Request&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;WriteString&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;w&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Hello, Go on Unit!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;})&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nx&#34;&gt;unit&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nf&#34;&gt;ListenAndServe&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;:8080&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;kc&#34;&gt;nil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;First, create a &lt;a href=&#34;https://go.dev/blog/using-go-modules&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Go module&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;code&gt;go get&lt;/code&gt; Unit&amp;rsquo;s package, and build your application:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Security checklist</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/security/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/security/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;At its core, Unit has security as one of its top priorities; our development&#xA;follows the appropriate best practices focused on making the code robust and&#xA;solid. However, even the most hardened system requires proper setup,&#xA;configuration, and maintenance.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This guide lists the steps to protect your Unit from installation to individual&#xA;app configuration.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote class=&#34;note&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br/&gt; The commands in this document starting with a hash (#) must be run as root or&#xA;with superuser privileges.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;security-update&#34;&gt;Update Unit regularly  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#security-update&#34; title=&#34;Update Unit regularly&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rationale&lt;/strong&gt;: Each release introduces &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/changes/&#34;&gt;bug fixes and new&#xA;features&lt;/a&gt; that improve your installation&amp;rsquo;s security.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Walkthrough</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/walkthrough/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/howto/walkthrough/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;OK, so you&amp;rsquo;ve decided to give Unit a try with your web app of choice. You may&#xA;be looking for ways to run it faster with less config overhead, streamlining&#xA;your technology stack, or simply be tech-curious. In any case:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;check-the-prerequisites&#34;&gt;Check the prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#check-the-prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Check the prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Verify that Unit&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx-unit/installation/#source-prereqs&#34;&gt;supports&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;your platform and app language version.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If possible, ensure the app can run beside Unit to rule out&#xA;external issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
